AIM:
To develop a simple application using Maven.

Procedure:
Start the process.

Create a Maven-based Java project:

Use maven-archetype-quickstart plug-in.

Create the project in C:\MVN directory.

Open the command console:

Ensure C:\MVN directory is empty.

Run the following command:

C:\MVN>mvn archetype:generate -DgroupId=com.companyname.bank -DartifactId=consumerBanking -DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart -DinteractiveMode=false
Verify Maven project structure:

Navigate to C:\MVN\consumerBanking.

Ensure project contains src folder and pom.xml.

Create source and test files:

src/main/java/com/companyname/bank/App.java:

java
package com.companyname.bank;
public class App {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello World!");
    }
}
src/test/java/com/companyname/bank/AppTest.java:

java
package com.companyname.bank;
import junit.framework.Test;
import junit.framework.TestCase;
import junit.framework.TestSuite;

public class AppTest extends TestCase {
    public AppTest(String testName) {
        super(testName);
    }
    public static Test suite() {
        return new TestSuite(AppTest.class);
    }
    public void testApp() {
        assertTrue(true);
    }
}
POM.xml:
xml
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">
    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>
    <groupId>com.companyname.projectgroup</groupId>
    <artifactId>project</artifactId>
    <version>1.0</version>
    <properties>
        <maven.compiler.source>11</maven.compiler.source>
        <maven.compiler.target>11</maven.compiler.target>
    </properties>
    <dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>junit</groupId>
            <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
            <version>3.8.1</version>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>
</project>
Util.java:
java
package com.companyname.bank;

public class Util {
    public static void printMessage(String message) {
        System.out.println(message);
    }
}
Modified App.java:
java
package com.companyname.bank;

public class App {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Util.printMessage("Hello World!");
    }
}
Output:
Compile and run:

Go to C:\MVN\consumerBanking directory.

Execute:

shell
mvn clean compile
java -cp com.companyname.bank.App Hello World!
Result:
Thus, the Maven simple application was compiled, built, and executed successfully.


consumerBanking/
|-- pom.xml
|-- src/
    |-- main/
    |   |-- java/
    |   |   `-- com/
    |   |       `-- companyname/
    |   |           `-- bank/
    |   |               `-- App.java
    |   `-- resources/
    |       `-- (resource files)
    `-- test/
        |-- java/
        |   `-- com/
        |       `-- companyname/
        |           `-- bank/
        |               `-- AppTest.java
        `-- resources/
            `-- (test resource files)

